@{PARD}
@{B}Unguarded Treasure Table Habitat/Society:@{UB}@{PAR}

None. UTTs are completely mindless, and therefore have no kind of social
tendencies whatsoever. They can be found in groups or alone, and there is no
good reason for it. They are, however, always found either indoors or
underground. They are NEVER found outdoors.@{PAR}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Ecology" "Unguarded Treasure Table Ecology"
@{CODE}	@{" Picture         " LINK "ImpPro:Data/ExtMonsterData/Unguarded Treasure Table.iff/main"}@{" Stats           " LINK "Stats"}
	@{" Combat          " LINK "Combat"}@{" Habitat/Society " LINK "Habitat"}@{" Ecology         " LINK "Ecology"}

@{PARD}
@{B}Unguarded Treasure Table Ecology:@{UB}@{PAR}

Unguarded Treasure Tables are not natural creatures, but nobody knows who or
what created them. They have no nice in nature, however they do tend to keep
dungeons of the tunnels-connecting-rooms variety clean of unguarded or dropped
treasure. Any treasure that is left unguarded in a dungeon with UTTs has a 5%
chance per hour (cumulative) of being discovered and eaten.@{PAR}

UTTs produce no worthwhile products, except for the treasure that they collect
and release upon "death". This is equal to ALL of the treasure types in the DMG,
at 90% chance for coinage, gems, and art objects (and any others) and 10% chance
for magic items, at listed amounts.@{PAR}

NOTE: Unguarded Treasure Tables are NOT for serious games!!!! (Duh!)@{PAR}

